28
[div class=p 
	[a href=http://desmume.org/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"DeSmuME
	]a
	" is a rerecording emulator used to create TAS movies for Nintendo DS games. The name is derived from "DS", "emu", and "ME".
	[a id=r1 
	]a
	[sup 
		"[
		[a href=#1 
			"1
		]a
		"]
	]sup
	" It has not been recommended for submissions since the release of the melonDS core in 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=BizHawk 2.7|href=/Bizhawk/ReleaseHistory#Bizhawk27)
	", but is still accepted.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=LatestVersion 
	" Latest Version
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	[a href=https://github.com/TASEmulators/desmume/releases/tag/release_0_9_13 rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"DeSmuME 0.9.13
	]a
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=DsMicrophoneInput 
	" DS microphone input
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"If your movie makes use of DS microphone audio input, 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=all the required audio data must be embedded into the movie|href=/MovieRules#DesmumeMovies)
	". For that purpose, use 
	[a href=https://github.com/TASEmulators/desmume/releases/tag/release_0_9_9a rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"DeSmuME version 0.9.9a
	]a
	". The steps required to embed .wav files into the movie:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" To embed a sample into the movie, go to 
		[em 
			"Config
		]em
		" - 
		[em 
			"Microphone Settings
		]em
		", check 
		[em 
			"Use Microphone Sample
		]em
		", select a wav file, and then start recording a new movie.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" To embed a series of samples, use the same base name for all of them, and to each of them add incrementing index starting with 0 and separated with an underscore, up to 255 sample files total. Example: 
		[code 
			"sample_0.wav
		]code
		" ... 
		[code 
			"sample_254.wav
		]code
		". Alternatively, just name the files after digital indexes. Example: 
		[code 
			"0.wav
		]code
		" ... 
		[code 
			"254.wav
		]code
		". Then select the 0th file in the series in the 
		[em 
			"Microphone Settings
		]em
		", and all the other files will be loaded automatically.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" To select the needed sample, use the hotkeys for 
		[em 
			"Mic Next Sample
		]em
		" and 
		[em 
			"Mic Prev Sample
		]em
		".
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Index of the currently selected sample is recorded at the corresponding movie frames.
	$LF
]div
